jp.ac.keio.bio.fun.xitosbml.xitosbml

Class SpatialSBMLExporter

  • java.lang.Object
    • jp.ac.keio.bio.fun.xitosbml.xitosbml.SpatialSBMLExporter

  • public class SpatialSBMLExporter
extends Object
    The class SpatialSBMLExporter, which converts a spatial model generated from microscopic images to an SBML model. Date Created: Feb 21, 2017
    Author:
    Kaito Ii <ii@fun.bio.keio.ac.jp>, Akira Funahashi <funa@bio.keio.ac.jp>

    • Method Detail

      • createGeometryElements

        public void createGeometryElements()
        Creates the geometry elements. This method will create following objects:
        • Geometry
        • CoordinateComponent
        • DomainType
        • Domain
        • AdjacentDomains
        • Compartment
        • CompartmentMapping
        • SampledFieldGeometry
        • SampledField
        • UnitDefinition
        • Unit
        CellDesigner annotation will be added in addOutside() method to support spatial modeling on CellDesigner.

      • addGeometryDefinitions

        public void addGeometryDefinitions()
        Adds the geometry definitions. This method supports creating both 2D and 3D spaces (by looking into DomainType). Each element in SampledField will store unsigned int 8 bit (uint8) value. Data compression is currently disabled.

      • compressRawData

        public byte[] compressRawData(byte[] raw)
        Compress raw data of spatial image in 1D array.
        Parameters:
        raw - the raw data of spatial image in 1D array
        Returns:
        byte[] the byte array

      • byteArrayToIntArray

        public int[] byteArrayToIntArray(byte[] compressed)
        Convert byte array to int array.
        Parameters:
        compressed - the compressed 1D byte array
        Returns:
        int[] the 1D integer array

      • addAdjacentDomains

        public void addAdjacentDomains()
        Adds the adjacent domains. This method adds membrane domains and adjacents to the model. The membrane domain contains a string "_membrane" in its SpatialId.

      • addDomains

        public void addDomains()
        Adds domains to corresponding domaintypes. If SpatialId contains a string "membrane", it will be handled as membrane domain, thus InteriorPoint will not be added to the domain.

      • getFromSpatialList

        public org.sbml.jsbml.ext.spatial.SpatialNamedSBase getFromSpatialList(org.sbml.jsbml.ListOf<?> list,
                                                                       String id)
        Returns SpatialNamedSBase object which has SpatialId "id" from given list of Objects. If there is no object in the list, then returns null.
        Parameters:
        list - list of objects (ex. SpatialNamedSbase)
        id - SpatialId
        Returns:
        SpatialNamedSBase object

      • addDomainTypes

        public void addDomainTypes()
        Adds the domain types to the Geometry object. SpatialId and SpatialDimensions will be set to generated domain type. Also, SpatialDimensions, SpatialId and its name will be added to the compartment.

      • addCoordinates

        public void addCoordinates()
        Adds the coordinates to the Geometry object. It alsow sets the minimum and maximum values of the coordinate axis (boundary) to a CoordinateComponent object which explicitly defines a coordinate component of the coordinate axes. If the image is a 3D image, then coordz (Z axis) will be set.

      • setCoordinateBoundary

        public void setCoordinateBoundary(org.sbml.jsbml.ext.spatial.CoordinateComponent coordinateComponent,
                                  String spId,
                                  double min,
                                  double max,
                                  double delta)
        Sets the minimum and maximum values of the coordinate axis (boundary) to a CoordinateComponent object which explicitly defines a coordinate component of the coordinate axes.
        Parameters:
        coordinateComponent - the CoordinateComponent object
        spId - the spatialId as String
        min - the minimum value of the coordinate axis
        max - the maximum value of the coordinate axis
        delta - the delta

      • addCoordParameter

        public void addCoordParameter()
        Adds the global Parameter to each CoordinateComponent. The id and the value of created will be set as "coordinate"+SpatialId and 0d respectively.

      • getModel

        public org.sbml.jsbml.Model getModel()
        Gets the SBML model.
        Returns:
        the SBML model

        Returns:
        the SBML document

      • addUnits

        public void addUnits()
        Adds the units (length, area and volume) to the model.

      • createParametric

        public void createParametric(HashMap<String,List<org.scijava.vecmath.Point3d>> hashVertices,
                             HashMap<String,org.scijava.vecmath.Point3d> hathBound)
        Creates the ParametricGeometry. This method will create following objects:
        • Geometry
        • CoordinateComponent
        • DomainType
        • Domain
        • AdjacentDomains
        • Compartment
        • CompartmentMapping
        • SpatialPoints
        • ParametricObject
        Parameters:
        hashVertices - the hashmap of vertices
        hathBound - the hashmap of boundary

      • addCoordinates

        public void addCoordinates(HashMap<String,org.scijava.vecmath.Point3d> hashBound)
        Adds the coordinates to the Geometry object. It alsow sets the minimum and maximum values of the coordinate axis (boundary) to a CoordinateComponent object which explicitly defines a coordinate component of the coordinate axes.
        Parameters:
        hashBound - the hashmap of boundary

      • addParaGeoDefinitions

        public void addParaGeoDefinitions(HashMap<String,List<org.scijava.vecmath.Point3d>> hashVertices,
                                  HashMap<String,org.scijava.vecmath.Point3d> hashBound)
        Adds the parametric geometry definitions. SpatialPoints will be set to ParametricGeometry. ParametricObject will store double value, and the polygon will be triangle. Data compression is currently disabled.
        Parameters:
        hashVertices - the hashmap of vertices
        hashBound - the hashmap of boundary

      • addUniqueVertices

        public void addUniqueVertices(org.sbml.jsbml.ext.spatial.SpatialPoints sp,
                              ArrayList<org.scijava.vecmath.Point3d> uniquePointSet)
        Adds the unique vertices to the SpatialPoints object. The set of unique vertices (an ArrayList of Point3d object: point0(x0, y0, z0), point1(x1, y1, z1) will be stored in an 1D array of String as ["x0", "y0", "z0", "x1", "y1", "z1", ...].
        Parameters:
        sp - the SpatialPoints of the ParametricGeometry
        uniquePointSet - the ArrayList of Point3d (unique point set)

      • setPointIndex

        public void setPointIndex(org.sbml.jsbml.ext.spatial.ParametricObject po,
                          List<org.scijava.vecmath.Point3d> list,
                          ArrayList<org.scijava.vecmath.Point3d> uniquePointSet)
        Sets the index of unique vertices to the SpatialPoints object. The set of index of unique vertices (an array of indices) will be stored in an 1D array of String as ["0", "3", "1", "2", ...].
        Parameters:
        po - the ParametricObject
        list - the list of Point3d
        uniquePointSet - the ArrayList of Point3d (unique point set)
